The paper discusses interference management and transmission rate improvement in multi-user networks, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The use of space-time block codes and multi-antenna channels suggests a possible connection to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also proposes new alignment methods, which could be considered a form of signal processing (cs.SI). The examples of interference networks suggest a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and computer engineering (cs.CE).
